d-prime
============================
$$d'={\frac {\mu _{S}-\mu _{N}}{\sqrt {{\frac {1}{2}}(\sigma _{S}^{2}+\sigma _{N}^{2})}}}$$
d=0 means we can not seperate the signal from noise.

